%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%224%20ways%20to%20fix%20Christmas%20lights%20if%20they're%20half%20out%20or%20don't%20work%20at%20all%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20buy%20through%20our%20links%2C%20Business%20Insider%20may%20earn%20an%20affiliate%20commission.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-reviews-expertise-in-product-reviews%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELearn%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20young%20child%20adding%20white%20string%20lights%20to%20a%20Christmas%20tree%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61a8fa600ed48c0019e55ea1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221060%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENothing%20puts%20a%20damper%20on%20holiday%20decorating%20like%20lights%20that%20won't%20light%20up.%3Cp%3ELiam%20Norris%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20top%20reason%20that%20indoor%20Christmas%20tree%20lights%20malfunction%20is%20an%20overloaded%20electrical%20circuit.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDiscard%20damaged%20bulbs%20promptly%20and%20replace%20them%20in%20order%20to%20extend%20the%20life%20of%20Christmas%20lights.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGive%20your%20string%20lights%20an%20end-of-the-season%20check-up%20to%20prevent%20future%20lighting%20problems.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELighting%20and%20trimming%20an%20indoor%20Christmas%20tree%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20treasured%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%20potentially%20troublesome%20%E2%80%94%20holiday%20traditions.%20If%20part%20of%20that%20tradition%20is%20the%20inevitable%20failure%20of%20a%20strand%20of%20lights%2C%20there%20are%20a%20few%20easy%20solutions%20you%20should%20try%20before%20you%20toss%20them%20into%20the%20trash.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBelow%2C%20Eddie%20Bello%2C%20owner%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.illuminationholidaylighting.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIlluminations%20Holiday%20Lighting%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Gary%20McCoy%2C%20store%20manager%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-151101663763h-20%26h%3D238a313e824c4ee4a27eced591f5798a1931509e9dc218e0ab5a426cad34d789%26postID%3D628f975fa2374776c7e8818b%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fhow-to-fix-christmas-lights%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.lowes.com%252F%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELowe's%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20walk%20us%20through%20how%20to%20troubleshoot%20Christmas%20light%20issues%2C%20so%20you%20can%20look%20forward%20to%20a%20bright%20holiday%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Check%20the%20circuit%20breaker%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221844%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20hand%20flipping%20the%20switch%20on%20a%20circuit%20breaker%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61a8fc865d47cc0018e9045e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221383%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EReset%20the%20circuit%20by%20turning%20the%20switch%20off%20and%20on%20again.%3Cp%3Elisafx%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20to%20try%20it%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhen%20none%20of%20the%20lights%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20none%20of%20the%20bulbs%20in%20a%20string%20of%20Christmas%20lights%20work%2C%20and%20you%20also%20notice%20that%20other%20lights%20in%20the%20same%20section%20of%20the%20house%20go%20out%2C%20you've%20likely%20tripped%20the%20circuit%20breaker%2C%20says%20Bello.%20An%20overloaded%20electrical%20circuit%20%E2%80%94%20a%20situation%20where%20more%20electrical%20demand%20is%20placed%20on%20an%20outlet%20than%20it%20can%20handle%20%E2%80%94%20is%20the%20most%20common%20(and%20least%20serious)%20reason%20for%20this%2C%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20check%20the%20circuit%20breaker%2C%20plug%20the%20lights%20into%20an%20electrical%20outlet.%20Next%2C%20reset%20the%20circuit%20breaker.%20To%20do%20this%2C%20locate%20the%20labeled%20circuit%20in%20the%20metal%20circuit%20box%20panel%2C%20which%20is%20usually%20found%20in%20your%20home's%20utility%20room%2C%20basement%2C%20or%20garage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20you%20locate%20the%20circuit%20you%20believe%20is%20tripped%20in%20the%20panel%2C%20move%20the%20switch%20all%20the%20way%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Boff%26quot%3B%20position%2C%20and%20then%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bon%26quot%3B%20position.%20You%20can%20often%20tell%20which%20circuit%20was%20tripped%20because%20the%20switch%20will%20be%20slightly%20out%20of%20alignment%20with%20the%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20bulbs%20light%20back%20up%2C%20an%20overloaded%20and%20tripped%20electrical%20circuit%20was%20likely%20your%20problem.%20This%20is%20good%20news%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20do%20anything%20further%2C%20other%20than%20taking%20care%20not%20to%20plug%20in%20multiple%20high-voltage%20electrical%20items%20simultaneously%20in%20the%20same%20area%20of%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Replace%20the%20fuse%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Colorful%20string%20lights%20in%20a%20pile%20with%20the%20plug%20open%20to%20expose%20the%20fuses%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61a8fcf45d47cc0018e90491%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221249%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EString%20light%20fuses%20are%20under%20a%20small%20panel%20on%20the%20plug.%3Cp%3EJJ%20Gouin%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20to%20try%20it%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhen%20the%20entire%20string%20won't%20light%20up%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20power%20coming%20from%20the%20outlet%20but%20your%20lights%20are%20not%20illuminating%2C%20it%20could%20be%20the%20result%20of%20a%20blown%20fuse%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Bello.%20Replacement%20fuses%20are%20often%20included%20when%20you%20purchase%20lights%2C%20but%20you%20can%20also%20buy%20them%20at%20most%20stores%20carrying%20holiday%20lights%2C%20says%20Bello.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20replace%20the%20fuse%2C%20slide%20open%20the%20lid%20on%20the%20back%20of%20the%20plug%20that%20inserts%20into%20the%20outlet.%20If%20the%20fuse%20is%20blown%2C%20one%20of%20the%20fuse%20tubes%20will%20likely%20appear%20black%20in%20color%20or%20have%20visible%20burn%20marks%2C%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETake%20a%20small%20tool%2C%20such%20as%20an%20eyeglass%20screwdriver%2C%20and%20pry%20out%20the%20fuses.%20Then%2C%20gently%20press%20in%20the%20new%20fuses.%20Close%20the%20cover%2C%20plug%20the%20lights%20in%2C%20and%20they%20should%20work.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBello%20notes%20that%20if%20the%20fuse%20blows%20again%2C%20it%20is%20likely%20due%20to%20damage%20in%20the%20light%20strand.%20If%20this%20happens%2C%20he%20says%20you%20should%20discard%20the%20lights%20and%20replace%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Replace%20burnt-out%20bulbs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20to%20try%20it%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhen%20individual%20bulbs%20or%20parts%20of%20the%20string%20won't%20light%20up%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20fuse%20isn't%20the%20problem%2C%20there%20is%20probably%20a%20problem%20with%20a%20bulb%2C%20says%20McCoy.%20To%20fix%20burnt-out%20bulbs%2C%20untangle%20all%20string%20lights%20and%20check%20for%20frayed%20wires%2C%20damaged%20sockets%2C%20or%20broken%20bulbs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDiscard%20any%20damaged%20bulbs%2C%20and%20then%20replace%20them%20with%20spare%20ones.%20%26quot%3BJust%20be%20sure%20to%20use%20bulbs%20with%20the%20same%20voltage%20rating%20as%20the%20rest%20of%20your%20string%20lights%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20McCoy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuick%20tip%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20To%20increase%20the%20lifespan%20of%20a%20string%20of%20lights%2C%20replace%20burnt-out%20bulbs%20promptly.%20Leaving%20burnt-out%20bulbs%20on%20a%20string%20of%20working%20lights%20increases%20stress%20on%20the%20working%20lights%2C%20and%20shortens%20their%20lifespan%2C%20explains%20McCoy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Test%20bulbs%20for%20damage%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20to%20try%20it%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhen%20no%20bulbs%20are%20visibly%20damaged%20and%20the%20lights%20aren't%20working%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20no%20bulbs%20are%20visibly%20damaged%2C%20and%20your%20lights%20are%20not%20working%2C%20use%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-151101663763h-20%26h%3D9e67deaaa4678bbc256ee6fd9d4a76f5f9f78fec95e50c016b3dc840c0946cee%26postID%3D628f975fa2374776c7e8818b%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fhow-to-fix-christmas-lights%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.lowes.com%252Fpd%252FHoliday-Living-Hl-Light-Tester-for-Led-Incandes%252F1001167814%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebulb%20tester%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20says%20McCoy.%20Follow%20the%20manufacturer's%20instructions%20to%20test%20each%20bulb.%20Once%20you%20find%20the%20faulty%20bulb%2C%20unplug%20the%20associated%20light%20strand%20from%20the%20outlet%20and%20replace%20the%20faulty%20bulb%20with%20a%20new%20bulb.%20Be%20sure%20to%20firmly%20seat%20each%20bulb%20in%20its%20socket%20when%20replacing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGive%20lights%20a%20post-holiday%20check-up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20sitting%20in%20front%20of%20a%20Christmas%20tree%20looking%20closely%20at%20a%20set%20of%20string%20lights%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61a8fe590ed48c0019e560db%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221060%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EInspect%20lights%20for%20any%20signs%20of%20damage%20before%20and%20after%20use.%3Cp%3ESolStock%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20great%20way%20to%20prevent%20future%20problems%20is%20to%20test%20your%20lights%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20season%2C%20says%20McCoy.%20As%20you%20take%20down%20each%20strand%20of%20lights%2C%20replace%20any%20burnt-out%20or%20broken%20bulbs.%20Throw%20away%20strands%20with%20broken%20or%20frayed%20cords.%20When%20it's%20time%20to%20trim%20the%20tree%20next%20year%2C%20your%20lights%20should%20all%20be%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuick%20tip%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20best%20way%20to%20store%20Christmas%20lights%20to%20prevent%20damage%20is%20to%20%26quot%3Bball%26quot%3B%20them%2C%20says%20Bello.%20%26quot%3BTo%20ball%20lights%2C%20hold%20the%20plug%20in%20your%20hand%20and%20wind%20the%20strand%20around%20your%20hand%20tightly%20to%20make%20a%20ball%20shape.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EInsider's%20takeaway%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChristmas%20light%20problems%20can%20quickly%20drain%20the%20joy%20out%20of%20your%20holiday%20decorating%20happiness.%20Tripped%20circuit%20breakers%2C%20blown%20fuses%2C%20and%20burnt-out%20bulbs%20are%20the%20most%20common%20problems%2C%20and%20thankfully%2C%20each%20one%20has%20a%20simple%20fix.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20you%20pack%20your%20Christmas%20decorations%20away%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20season%2C%20give%20your%20string%20lights%20a%20post-holiday%20checkup.%20That%20way%2C%20you'll%20look%20forward%20to%20a%20bright%20and%20trouble-free%20holiday%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhow-to-fix-christmas-lights%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1777267424000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61a8fa580ed48c0019e55e8f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fh