3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Prepare%20your%20steam%20cleaner.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Read%20your%20furniture%20steam%20cleaner's%20manual%20and%20fill%20it%20with%20the%20appropriate%20amount%20of%20water%20and%20upholstery%20cleaning%20fluid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Plug%20in%20your%20machine%20and%20turn%20it%20on.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Depending%20on%20your%20machine%20you%20may%20need%20to%20wait%20for%20it%20to%20heat%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Clean%20the%20cushions%20first.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Once%20heated%2C%20use%20the%20handheld%20piece%20to%20steam%20clean%20the%20cushions%20first%20by%20spraying%20the%20water%20and%20cleaner%20mixture%20onto%20a%20small%20section%20and%20dragging%20the%20hose%20over%20a%20small%20area%20at%20a%20time%20to%20steam%20and%20suck%20up%20the%20dirt%20and%20dampness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Clean%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20couch.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Repeat%20this%20process%20over%20each%20section%20of%20the%20couch%2C%20being%20sure%20to%20steam%20small%20sections%20at%20a%20time%20so%20no%20area%20stays%20wet%20for%20an%20extended%20period%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Allow%20time%20for%20it%20to%20dry.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20This%20may%20vary%20depending%20on%20the%20air%20circulation%20in%20your%20space%20but%20opening%20windows%20or%20blowing%20a%20fan%20can%20help%20speed%20up%20this%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImportant%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBefore%20using%20a%20new%20solution%20on%20any%20furniture%20material%2C%20be%20sure%20to%20test%20it%20on%20an%20inconspicuous%20area%20to%20make%20sure%20it%20doesn't%20cause%20discoloration%20or%20damage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228bcb8490-ac58-420c-b19a-72a1ed4444f2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20spot-treat%20couch%20stains%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221883%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Red%20wine%20spilled%20on%20a%20couch%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F60ad6cefbee0fc0019d5974e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221412%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBlot%20gently%20to%20remove%20as%20much%20of%20a%20stain%20as%20you%20can.%3Cp%3EVershinin%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESpills%20and%20spots%20should%20be%20treated%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%20for%20the%20highest%20chance%20at%20preventing%20long-lasting%20stains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20starters%2C%20if%20your%20couch%20has%20cushion%20and%20pillow%20covers%2C%20remove%20them%20immediately%20so%20the%20liquid%20doesn't%20soak%20through%20into%20the%20insert.%20Then%2C%20absorb%20as%20much%20of%20the%20spill%20from%20the%20cover%20as%20possible%20with%20a%20dry%20cloth.%20If%20your%20couch%20can%20get%20wet%20(again%2C%20check%20the%20label)%2C%20you%20should%20then%20%26quot%3Bblot%20%5Bit%5D%20with%20cool%20water%20and%20add%20a%20little%20castile%20soap%20if%20needed%2C%26quot%3B%20Rapinchuk%20instructs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou'll%20need%20to%20follow%20a%20different%20cleaning%20method%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20stain.%20Here%20are%20some%20of%20the%20most%20common%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EUrine%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ETo%20remove%20urine%20from%20your%20couch%2C%20gently%20dab%20(don't%20press%20too%20hard%20or%20you'll%20spread%20the%20stain)%20a%20homemade%20solution%20of%201%20to%202%20cups%20of%20water%2C%201%20teaspoon%20of%20vinegar%2C%20and%201%20teaspoon%20of%20dish%20soap%20on%20the%20stain.%20Rinse%20and%20repeat%20as%20needed%20until%20the%20spot%20is%20completely%20removed.%20To%20treat%20the%20smell%2C%20follow%20this%20cleaning%20process%20with%20a%20spray%20solution%20consisting%20of%201%20cup%20water%2C%20%C2%BD%20cup%20dish%20soap%2C%20%C2%BE%20cup%20peroxide%2C%20and%20about%2020%20drops%20of%20your%20preferred%20essential%20oil(s)%20on%20the%20area.%20Finish%20by%20patting%20the%20spot%20completely%20dry%20with%20a%20clean%20cloth.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EBlood%20and%20grease%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ETreat%20blood%20and%20grease%20spots%20by%20soaking%20them%20up%20with%20cool%20water%20and%20massaging%20in%20a%20drop%20of%20soap.%20Unless%20your%20care%20instructions%20tell%20you%20not%20to%2C%20try%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-1511016106852-20%26h%3D0b4f9e78c69681dbf27d842444bc209fc92fa1a586bc1f62cf08f4926d8ac27e%26postID%3D628f975fa2374776c7e881cf%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fhow-to-clean-a-couch%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252Fgp%252Fproduct%252FB00ISDMQ8U%252Fref%253Das_li_tl%253Fie%253DUTF8%2526amp%253Btag%253Dbihk_052521_how-to-clean-couch-20%2526amp%253Bcamp%253D1789%2526amp%253Bcreative%253D9325%2526amp%253BlinkCode%253Das2%2526amp%253BcreativeASIN%253DB00ISDMQ8U%2526amp%253BlinkId%253D2d7f08872576625d07f08bf0ff4d472b%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenzyme%20stain%20remover%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20break%20down%20the%20proteins%20and%20a%20degreaser%20such%20as%20dish%20soap%20for%20grease%20stains.%20If%20all%20else%20fails%20and%20the%20blood%20and%20grease%20have%20seeped%20deeply%20into%20the%20couch%20fabric%2C%20try%20using%20a%20cotton%20swab%20dipped%20in%20hydrogen%20peroxide%20only%20on%20the%20stained%20area.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EFood%2C%20wine%2C%20and%20coffee%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECleaning%20up%20food%20and%20wine%20stains%20from%20a%20couch%20will%20require%20a%20very%20similar%20approach%20to%20blood%20or%20grease.%20Blot%20away%20the%20excess%20food%20or%20moisture%20with%20a%20dry%20cloth%20then%20soak%20up%20the%20remaining%20stain%20with%20cool%20water%20and%20a%20drop%20of%20soap.%20If%20approved%20of%20by%20the%20cleaning%20label%2C%20use%20an%20acidic%20stain%20remover%20to%20get%20stubborn%20coffee%2C%20wine%2C%20and%20food%20stains%20out%20%E2%80%94%20or%2C%20as%20a%20last%20resort%2C%20use%20the%20same%20cotton%20swab%20and%20hydrogen%20peroxide%20method%20outlined%20above.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EPet%20hair%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFrom%20one%20pet%20owner%20to%20another%2C%20Chartrand%20recommends%20using%20a%20fur-specific%20vacuum%20attachment%20or%20even%20a%20pet%20fur%20squeegee%20to%20remove%20pet%20hair%20from%20your%20furniture.%20Should%20neither%20of%20these%20be%20an%20option%20for%20you%2C%20though%2C%20a%20lint%20roller%20or%20even%20the%20sticky%20side%20of%20packing%20tape%20should%20do%20the%20trick.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227df420ab-bb23-4925-b326-d275e3d44633%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20often%20do%20you%20need%20to%20clean%20a%20couch%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20deep%20cleaning%20your%20couch%2C%20Rapinchuk%20recommends%20vacuuming%2C%20spot%20cleaning%2C%20and%20rotating%20and%20flipping%20the%20cushions%20seasonally%20to%20keep%20it%20as%20fresh%20as%20can%20be.%20For%20couches%20and%20sofas%20used%20daily%2C%20you%20may%20want%20to%20consider%20two%20or%20more%20times%20per%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChartrand%20adds%20that%20if%20your%20couch%20has%20removable%20pillow%20cushion%20covers%2C%20they%20can%20be%20washed%20monthly%20or%20even%20every%20couple%20of%20weeks%20depending%20on%20their%20condition%E2%80%94just%20check%20the%20label%20to%20determine%20whether%20you%20need%20to%20hand%20wash%2C%20machine%20wash%2C%20or%20dry%20clean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2231baae10-d048-4799-83c0-c91e967583b5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20maintain%20your%20couch%20between%20cleanings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20thoroughly%20deep%20cleaning%20your%20couches%20seasonally%20will%20help%20them%20last%20longer%2C%20vacuuming%2C%20lint%20rolling%2C%20and%2For%20wiping%20down%20your%20couches%20weekly%20will%20help%20with%20upkeep.%20Unless%20otherwise%20instructed%20on%20the%20care%20label%2C%20both%20Rapinchuk%20and%20Chartrand%20recommend%20using%20a%20steam%20cleaner%20on%20your%20couches%20to%20deep%20clean%20and%20sanitize%20them.%20It's%20worth%20the%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuick%20tip%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20my%20favorite%20tips%20is%20taking%20a%20couple%20of%20dryer%20sheets%20and%20adding%20them%20inside%20the%20couch%20cushion%20covers%20to%20keep%20everything%20smelling%20fresh%2C%26quot%3B%20Chartrand%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fe74859d-b56c-40bc-9e18-3b30aca3aad2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EInsider's%20takeaway%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECleaning%20your%20couch%20may%20seem%20exhausting%20at%20first%2C%20but%20if%20you%20read%20the%20care%20label%20thoroughly%2C%20follow%20the%20instructions%2C%20and%20spot%20test%20any%20solutions%20you're%20unsure%20about%20before%20using%2C%20you'll%20do%20just%20fine.%20The%20easiest%20way%20to%20take%20care%20of%20your%20couch%20is%20to%20make%20upkeep%20a%20part%20of%20your%20weekly%20chores%3A%20vacuum%20it%20regularly%2C%20wash%20any%20covers%20as%20directed%2C%20and%20treat%20stains%20as%20they%20pop%20up%20(don't%20wait).%20This%20will%20make%20those%20seasonal%20deep%20cleans%20a%20whole%20lot%20easier%20%E2%80%94%20and%20less%20dreadful.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20those%20deep%20cleans%2C%20steam%20cleaners%20are%20definitely%20the%20key%20to%20simplifying%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhow-to-clean-a-couch%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1777266961000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F60ad6f66bee0fc0019d59768%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhow-to-clean-a-couch%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Vacuuming%20and%20spot-treating%20stains%20regularly%20will%20help%20make%20seasonal%20deep-cleans%20of%20a%20fabric%20couch%20much%20easier.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Taylor%20Mead)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20brought%20an%20old%20leather%20chair%20back%20to%20life%20using%20these%20products%20and%20the%20transformation%20is%20incredible%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20buy%20through%20our%20links%2C%20Business%20Insider%20may%20earn%20an%20affiliate%20commission.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-reviews-expertise-in-product-reviews%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELearn%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221704%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20leather%20armchair%20that%20has%20been%20cleaned%20with%20Clyde's%20Leather%20Cleaning%20Foam.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F628541f8e19cda0018867a82%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221278%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBrenna%20Darling%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI%20had%20a%20worn%20antique%20leather%20armchair%20that%20needed%20to%20be%20revived.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20used%20products%20from%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclydesleathercompany.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClyde's%20Leather%20Company%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20transform%20the%20chair%20into%20one%20that%20looks%20brand%20new.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20leather%20restoring%20products%20are%20a%20cost-effective%20way%20to%20extend%20the%20life%20of%20existing%20leather.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20inherited%20a%20beautiful%20leather%20armchair%20from%20my%20grandfather%20after%20he%20passed%20away%20last%20year.%20This%20chair%20is%20between%2050%20and%2080%20years%20old%20%E2%80%94%20my%20father%20recalls%20seeing%20it%20in%20his%20own%20grandparents'%20home%20as%20a%20child.%C2%A0%20It's%20very%20sentimental%20to%20me%20and%20makes%20me%20think%20of%20him%20each%20time%20I%20sit%20in%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20chair%20has%20aged%20quite%20a%20bit%2C%20with%20cracks%20on%20the%20armrests%20and%20the%20seat%20cushion%2C%20and%20the%20original%20leather%20has%20faded%20into%20a%20strange%20yellow%20color.%C2%A0After%20doing%20quite%20a%20bit%20of%20research%20on%20leather%20restoration%2C%20I%20found%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclydesleathercompany.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClyde's%20Leather%20Company%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20decided%20to%20try%20its%20products%20to%20revive%20my%20armchair.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EOur%20review%20of%20Clyde's%20Leather%20Company%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClyde's%20Leather%20Company%20offers%20a%20variety%20of%20products%20to%20repair%20both%20leather%20and%20vinyl.%20Everything%20from%20shoes%20to%20car%20upholstery%20can%20benefit%20from%20the%20company's%20products.%20Depending%20on%20a%20project's%20size%2C%20the%20process%20can%20take%20anywhere%20from%20a%20few%20hours%20to%20a%20few%20days.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EI%20restored%20my%20leather%20chair%20with%204%20products%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221704%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Clyde's%20Interior%20Cleaning%20Foam%2C%20Recoloring%20Balm%2C%20and%20Conditioning%20Cream%20on%20a%20leather%20chair.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62854b02e19cda0018867ccf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221278%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBrenna%20Darling%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20chair%20restoration%20project%20required%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiauto-55327-20%26h%3Dd7f8b36979f696510e247e2f788cfd68aaa140ffe035344b7a238eb7795b7bf7%26postID%3D628541a31da02b7e444b36b2%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fclydes-leather-company-review%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252Fdp%252FB09WLD292V%5C%22%2