st.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClyde's%20Recoloring%20Balms%20are%20available%20in%20multiple%20colors.%20I%20tried%20out%20three%20samples%20before%20deciding%20on%20dark%20brown.%20If%20you%20don't%20see%20a%20color%20that%20matches%20your%20item%2C%20they%20can%20work%20with%20you%20to%20mix%20the%20perfect%20custom%20shade.%20They%20send%20everything%20you%20need%20to%20complete%20your%20leather%20repair%2C%20including%20gloves%2C%20sponges%2C%20and%20brushes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EStep%201%3A%20I%20determined%20whether%20the%20leather%20on%20my%20armchair%20was%20absorbent%20or%20if%20it%20had%20a%20coating%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221704%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20glass%20of%20water%20sitting%20on%20the%20arm%20of%20a%20leather%20chair.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62854b681aa29100196a4eae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221278%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBrenna%20Darling%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20instructions%2C%20I%20added%20a%20small%20droplet%20of%20water%20to%20the%20armrest.%20If%20the%20leather%20had%20no%20coating%2C%20it%20would%20have%20absorbed%20right%20away.%20In%20my%20case%2C%20the%20water%20did%20not%20absorb%2C%20indicating%20that%20I%20would%20need%20to%20use%20Clyde's%20Deglazer%20before%20applying%20the%20Recoloring%20Balm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EStep%202%3A%20I%20thoroughly%20cleaned%20the%20leather%20with%20the%20Interior%20Cleaning%20Foam%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221704%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20person%20using%20a%20cloth%20to%20apply%20the%20Clyde's%20Leather%20Interior%20Cleaning%20Foam%20to%20the%20arm%20of%20a%20leather%20chair.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62854ba3e19cda0018867d16%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221278%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBrenna%20Darling%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20the%20process%20could%20begin.%20I%20used%20Clyde's%20Interior%20Cleaning%20Foam%20and%20a%20microfiber%20cloth%20to%20clean%20the%20chair%2C%20making%20sure%20to%20get%20in%20all%20the%20nooks%20and%20crannies.%20After%20patting%20it%20down%20and%20giving%20it%20about%2020%20minutes%20to%20dry%2C%20I%20vacuumed%20up%20any%20leftover%20dust%20and%20debris%20for%20good%20measure.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EStep%203%3A%20I%20removed%20the%20existing%20coating%20from%20the%20leather%20using%20the%20Deglazer%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENext%20was%20the%20deglazing%20step.%20I%20used%20a%20combination%20of%20cotton%20pads%20and%20a%20cotton%20towel%2C%20plus%20Clyde's%20Deglazer%2C%20to%20get%20the%20top%20coating%20off%20of%20my%20chair.%20It%20actually%20came%20off%20black%2C%20which%20was%20very%20helpful%20as%20I%20could%20see%20each%20area%20that%20needed%20attention.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221704%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20person%20applying%20the%20Clyde's%20Leather%20Prep%20and%20Deglazer%20on%20a%20leather%20cushion.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62854bd91aa29100196a4ef1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221278%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBrenna%20Darling%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EStep%204%3A%20I%20applied%20the%20Recoloring%20Balm%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20chair%20had%20fully%20dried%20from%20the%20deglazing%2C%20I%20began%20with%20the%20Recoloring%20Balm.%20Clyde's%20provides%20gloves%20for%20this%20step%2C%20which%20I%20highly%20recommend%20to%20avoid%20staining%20your%20fingers.%20I%20used%20the%20accompanying%20sponge%20to%20rub%20the%20balm%20in%20a%20circular%20motion%20into%20the%20leather.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20dried%20very%20quickly%2C%20so%20I%20could%20add%20a%20second%20coat%20within%20an%20hour.%20Clyde's%20recommends%20repeating%20this%20step%20until%20the%20desired%20color%20is%20achieved.%20For%20me%2C%20it%20was%20two%20coats%2C%20and%20I%20used%20about%20two%20jars%20of%20the%20balm.%20I%20then%20let%20the%20new%20color%20cure%20for%20at%20least%2024%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221704%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20person%20wearing%20plastic%20gloves%20to%20apply%20the%20Clyde's%20Recoloring%20Balm%20to%20a%20sponge%20to%20use%20on%20a%20leather%20chair.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62854c151aa29100196a4f28%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221278%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBrenna%20Darling%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EStep%205%3A%20I%20used%20the%20Remoisturizing%20Cream%20to%20give%20the%20leather%20a%20clean%2C%20protective%20finish%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20step%20is%20crucial%20to%20add%20a%20protective%20finish%20to%20the%20recolored%20leather.%20I%20applied%20it%20with%20the%20provided%20brush%20and%20could%20literally%20see%20the%20cracks%20in%20the%20leather%20soaking%20up%20the%20product.%20Made%20with%20a%20mixture%20of%20beeswax%20and%20naturally%20occurring%20lipids%20and%20seed%20oils%2C%20it%20was%20extremely%20satisfying%20to%20see%20it%20repair%20my%20chair.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221704%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20hand%20displaying%20an%20opened%20tin%20of%20the%20Clyde's%20Conditioning%20Cream.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62854c3e1aa29100196a4f3f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221278%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBrenna%20Darling%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20we%20like%20about%20Clyde's%20Leather%20Company%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20comparison%20of%20a%20leather%20chair%20before%20and%20after%20getting%20a%20restoration%20treatment%20with%20products%20from%20Clyde's.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62854ce21aa29100196a4fa6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBrenna%20Darling%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20love%20that%2C%20at%20a%20relatively%20low%20cost%2C%20the%20Clyde's%20products%20gave%20my%20chair%20a%20complete%20face%20lift.%20I'm%20blown%20away%20that%20it%20will%20now%20have%20a%20long%20life%20ahead.%20The%20color%20is%20rich%20and%20beautifully%20saturated%2C%20and%20the%20cracks%20in%20the%20arms%20and%20seat%20are%20completely%20gone.%20It's%20been%20about%20two%20weeks%20since%20I%20applied%20the%20products%20and%20I'm%20pleased%20to%20say%20that%20it's%20holding%20up%20well%20and%20it%20continues%20to%20be%20my%20favorite%20reading%20spot.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EThe%20cons%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%20bit%20of%20trial%20and%20error%20on%20my%20part%20as%20I%20began%20the%20project.%20The%20instructions%20could%20have%20been%20clearer%2C%20either%20on%20the%20website%20or%20sent%20with%20the%20products.%20For%20example%2C%20I%20couldn't%20find%20any%20information%20on%20how%20long%20the%20Remoisturizing%20Cream%20needed%20to%20dry.%20Since%20the%20Recoloring%20Balm%20recommended%20a%2024-hour%20cure%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20give%20that%20a%20shot%20for%20the%20cream.%20I%20would%20have%20loved%20to%20have%20a%20definitive%20answer%20though.%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EThe%20bottom%20line%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20highly%20recommend%20Clyde's%20Leather%20Company%20for%20anyone%20who%20needs%20to%20refresh%20a%20leather%20product.%20Attempting%20to%20repair%20my%20leather%20chair%20was%20more%20cost-effective%20and%20environmentally%20friendly%20than%20purchasing%20something%20new.%20I'll%20be%20able%20to%20enjoy%20sitting%20in%20the%20armchair%20for%20years%20to%20come.%20I'd%20like%20to%20think%20that%20my%20grandpa%20would%20be%20pretty%20excited%20to%20see%20how%20his%20chair%20looks%2C%20after%20all%20these%20years.%20I%20wonder%20if%20he'd%20even%20recognize%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPros%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECost-effective%2C%20user-friendly%2C%20highly%20transformative%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECons%3A%20